news.title: Web portal displaying layout plans of Delhi launched by DDA
news.para: The central government under its Ease of Doing Business vision has initiated to get all layout plans of Delhi digitised and developed a web portal where approved layout plans are uploaded, the DDA said in a statement.

news.title: IWG to merge digital assets with The Instant Group
news.para: IWG's decision comes at a time when office landlords are slowly recovering as tenants reassess their options following the COVID-19 pandemic, including a shift to a permanent hybrid model, in which employees split work between home and office.

news.title: Gurugram: Chintels stopped from selling apartments under its seven projects
news.para: "The projects concerned are Chintels Paradiso-12.306 acres Group Housing and Chintels Serenity- 20.169 acres Group Housing in sector 109; Chintels Corporate Parks- 3.2 acres in sector 114; Shoba City- 39.379 acres Group Housing in sector 108, among others. The said projects are under Chintels India Limited, Chintels Export Pvt. Ltd, Ashok Solomon and Intels India Pvt. Ltd," the order stated.

news.title: Proptech startup Propdial raises Rs 1 crore via compulsory convertible debentures
news.para: This top-up is a part of the funding round to which Propdial raised Rs 1 crore last year in November. Prior to this, the company had also raised seed funding last year.

news.title: Gurugram: Councillors to tell residents about change in norms
news.para: In order to enhance the number of applications for the regularisation of colonies, the municipal corporation of Gurgaon (MCG) has decided to involve councillors to apprise the residents about the change in norms for such colonies.

news.title: Construction & demolition waste to be picked from doorstep in Faridabad by March end
news.para: The district disclosed its action plan to mitigate air pollution on Monday at the “Dialogue Towards Clean Air”, a two-day event. It also aims to clean and remove encroachment from stormwater drains and is planning to designate street vendor zones in the next 15 days.

news.title: Sebi to auction properties of Royal Twinkle, Citrus Check Inns on April 6
news.para: The properties to go under the hammer include office premises, residential flats, land parcels, shops located in Maharashtra, Gujarat, Daman and Dadra and Nagar Haveli.

news.title: About 24,000 defaulters owe Rs 85 crore to Chandigarh housing board
news.para: The list includes owners of small flats given under slum rehabilitation schemes; affordable rental housing schemes (ARHC), also given to slum dwellers ; commercial and residential flats in different sectors and colonies.

news.title: Credai Nashik asks state government not to hike ready reckoner rate
news.para: Credai has sent a letter in this regard to the state government along with the local MLAs, urging them to do their best for keeping the RR rates unchanged.

news.title: Indore development body to construct residential & commercial buildings
news.para: “In the board meeting, we have approved developing five new schemes after clearing around 700 claims and objections received in this regard” the chairman Jaypal Singh Chawda said, adding that the proposals have been sent to the state government for its consent.

news.title: Haryana urban local bodies department set to regularise 845 illegal colonies
news.para: Urban local bodies minister Kamal Gupta said the town and country planning department had invited online applications for regularizing colonies from resident welfare associations and developers.

news.title: Telangana government to give Rs 3 lakh aid to poor to build 2BHK house
news.para: While 3,000 beneficiaries in each Assembly constituency would be covered, the MLAs will have allotment authority for 3.57 lakh beneficiaries in all and the remaining 43,000 would be at the discretion of CM KCR.

news.title: Pune: Building permission department may not remain cash cow next fiscal
news.para: The commissioner’s budget reduced the revenue target of the Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) department substantially to Rs1,400 crore for the 2022-23 financial year.

news.title: Demand for satellite, boutique offices surge post pandemic
news.para: Several factors including caution towards capital expenditure, need for flexibility in lease terms and allowing mobility to workforce as organisations await more clarity in business conditions and workplace strategies are helping push the demand for satellite offices.

news.title: Delhi development authority's survey in 87 slums to help find them new homes
news.para: Around 20 lakh people live in 677 slum clusters out of which 490 are on land belonging to DDA and the central government.
